    (SID_DESC =
      (GLOBAL_DBNAME = CDB1)
      (ORACLE_HOME = /u01/app/oracle/product/21c/dbhome_1)
      (SID_NAME = CDB1)
    )
  )
Step 3: Duplicate the Primary Database to StandbyOn the , start the database in :Use RMAN from the  to duplicate:rman TARGET sys@CDB1 AUXILIARY sys@CDB1_STBY
DUPLICATE TARGET DATABASE FOR STANDBY FROM ACTIVE DATABASE
DORECOVER
SPFILE
SET DB_UNIQUE_NAME='CDB1_STBY'
SET LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_2='SERVICE=CDB1 ASYNC VALID_FOR=(ONLINE_LOGFILES,PRIMARY_ROLE) DB_UNIQUE_NAME=CDB1_STBY'
SET LOG_ARCHIVE_DEST_STATE_2=ENABLE;
Step 4: Enable Data Guard BrokerALTER SYSTEM SET DG_BROKER_START=TRUE;
ALTER SYSTEM SET DG_BROKER_START=TRUE;
Step 5: Configure Data Guard BrokerCreate Broker ConfigurationOn Primary Database (in Dataguard Broker):dgmgrl /
CREATE CONFIGURATION 'DGBROKER' AS PRIMARY DATABASE IS 'CDB1' CONNECT IDENTIFIER IS 'CDB1';
ADD DATABASE 'CDB1_STBY' AS CONNECT IDENTIFIER IS 'CDB1_STBY' MAINTAINED AS PHYSICAL;
ENABLE CONFIGURATION;
EXIT;
Verify Configuration (in Dataguard Broker)dgmgrl /
SHOW CONFIGURATION;
SHOW DATABASE VERBOSE 'CDB1_STBY';
EXIT;
To test, perform a switchover:dgmgrl /
SWITCHOVER TO 'CDB1_STBY';
EXIT;
dgmgrl /
SHOW CONFIGURATION;
EXIT;
Validating Standby Database Synchronization with PrimaryOnce the standby database is built, ensure that it stays in sync with the primary by following these steps.1. Verify Redo Log Archival on PrimaryRun the following SQL query on the  database to determine the current redo log sequence numbers:SELECT thread#, sequence#, archived, status FROM v$log;
THREAD#   SEQUENCE#  ARC  STATUS
--------  ---------  ---  ------
       1        947  YES   ACTIVE
       1        948  NO    CURRENT
Check the most recently archived redo log file:SELECT MAX(sequence#) FROM v$archived_log;
MAX(SEQUENCE#)
--------------
          947
2. Validate Redo Log Shipping to StandbyCheck the archive destinations to confirm logs are being sent to the standby:SELECT destination, status, archived_thread#, archived_seq#
FROM v$archive_dest_status
WHERE status <> 'DEFERRED' AND status <> 'INACTIVE';
DESTINATION         STATUS  ARCHIVED_THREAD#  ARCHIVED_SEQ#
------------------  ------  ----------------  -------------
/private1/prmy/lad   VALID                 1            947
standby1             VALID                 1            947
Ensure the  is the same across all destinations.If the status is not , investigate further.3. Verify Log Gaps at StandbyRun the following SQL on the  database:SELECT thread#, MAX(sequence#) FROM v$archived_log GROUP BY thread#;
Ensure that the  matches the primary.4. Check Apply Lag on StandbyOn the standby, check the last applied redo log:SELECT thread#, sequence#, applied FROM v$archived_log WHERE applied='YES';
If there is a lag, check the  (Managed Recovery Process) status:  SELECT process, status, sequence# FROM v$managed_standby WHERE process='MRP0';
5. Check Standby Database StatusEnsure the standby is in :SELECT database_role, open_mode FROM v$database;
DATABASE_ROLE    OPEN_MODE
---------------  ------------
PHYSICAL STANDBY MOUNTED
If it's not in  mode, start recovery:ALTER DATABASE RECOVER MANAGED STANDBY DATABASE DISCONNECT FROM SESSION;
6. Check Data Guard ConfigurationSELECT * FROM v$dataguard_status;
Look for any errors or inconsistencies.With these steps, you have successfully set up  using  in Oracle 21c. This provides an automated failover mechanism and ensures .

When you ignore your inheritance, you will have trouble with your parentsTL;DR: Subclasses should honor ALL their parent’s contract.Favor composition over inheritanceWhen you create a subclass, it should use or extend the behavior of its parent.\
If it ignores or overrides most of it, you probably force inheritance where it doesn’t belong to reuse code.\
This makes the code misleading and hard to maintain.class House {
  constructor(address) {
    this.address = address;
  }
  address() {
    return this.address;
  }
  openDoor() {
    console.log("Door opened at " + this.address);
  }
}

class Motorhome extends House {
  constructor() {
    super(null);
  }
  address() {
    return null;
    // This implementation is the same as the parent's
    // and is also a refused bequest
  }
  openDoor() {
    console.log("Motorhome door opened.");
  }
}
class House {
  constructor(address) {
    this.address = address;
  }
  address() {
    return this.address;
  }
  openDoor() {
    console.log("Door opened at " + this.address);
  }
}

class Motorhome {
  // does not inherit from House
  constructor(gps) {
    this.gps = gps;
  }
  openDoor() {
    console.log("Motorhome door opened at " + this.gps.getLocation());
  }
}
Look for subclasses that override or ignore most of their parent’s behavior.\
You should reconsider the inheritance if a subclass sets parent properties to null or reimplements core methods.Your software should reflect real-world relationships.\
When you force a subclass that doesn’t logically extend its parent in the Bijection, you mislead developers and introduce maintenance problems.AI can generate this smell when it defaults to inheritance for reuse instead of composition.\
This happens when AI follows generic templates without understanding the context.AI can detect this smell by analyzing class structures and inheritance trees. However, it struggles with subtle cases where inheritance initially seems valid but breaks expectations.Remember: AI Assistants make lots of mistakesWhen you design a class hierarchy, you need to make sure that subclasses logically inherit from their parent.\
If a subclass refuses some of the behavior, you should rethink your design.Favor object composition over class inheritance.This article is part of the CodeSmell Series.
